msgstr "Monks’ Confession 41"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:0.5"
msgid "41. Acelakasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on naked ascetics"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.91, pts-cs-bu-pc41.1.1, pts-vp-en.2.347, ms2V_866 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena saṃghassa khādanīyaṃ ussannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time the Order was receiving an abundance of non-staple food."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda told the Master, who said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.4"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, vighāsādānaṃ pūvaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, give the biscuits to those who take leftovers.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā vighāsāde paṭipāṭiyā nisīdāpetvā ekekaṃ pūvaṃ dento aññatarissā paribbājikāya ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsi."
msgstr "“Yes, Venerable Sir.” Ānanda got them to sit in a row and gave them one biscuit each, until he accidentally gave two to a female wanderer."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.6"
msgid "Sāmantā paribbājikāyo taṃ paribbājikaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The female wanderers sitting next to her said to her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.7"
msgid "“jāro te eso samaṇo”ti."
msgstr "“This ascetic is your lover.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.8"
msgid "“Na me so samaṇo jāro, ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsī”ti."
msgstr "“He’s not. He gave me two, thinking they were one.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.9"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "And a second time …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.10"
msgid "tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando ekekaṃ pūvaṃ dento tassāyeva paribbājikāya ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsi."
msgstr "And a third time Ānanda gave them one biscuit each, until he accidentally gave two to that same female wanderer."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.11"
msgid "Sāmantā paribbājikāyo taṃ paribbājikaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Once again the female wanderers sitting next to her said to her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.12"
msgid "“jāro te eso samaṇo”ti."
msgstr "“This ascetic is your lover.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.13"
msgid "“Na me so samaṇo jāro, ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsī”ti."
msgstr "“He’s not. He gave me two, thinking they were one.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.1.14"
msgid "“Jāro na jāro”ti bhaṇḍiṃsu."
msgstr "And they started to argue about whether or not they were lovers."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs-bu-pc41.1.2 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.1"
msgid "Aññataropi ājīvako parivesanaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "A certain Ājīvaka ascetic, too, went to that distribution of food."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.2"
msgid "Aññataro bhikkhu pahūtena sappinā odanaṃ madditvā tassa ājīvakassa mahantaṃ piṇḍaṃ adāsi."
msgstr "A monk mixed rice with a large amount of ghee and gave him a large lump."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.348 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.3"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako taṃ piṇḍaṃ ādāya agamāsi."
msgstr "He took it and left."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.4"
msgid "Aññataro ājīvako taṃ ājīvakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Another Ājīvaka asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.5"
msgid "“kuto tayā, āvuso, piṇḍo laddho”ti?"
msgstr "“Where did you get that lump?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.6"
msgid "“Tassāvuso, samaṇassa gotamassa muṇḍagahapatikassa parivesanāya laddho”ti."
msgstr "“From the food distribution of the ascetic Gotama, that shaven-headed lay person.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.92, ms2V_867 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.7"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho upāsakā tesaṃ ājīvakānaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr "Some lay followers overheard that conversation between those Ājīvaka ascetics."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.8"
msgid "Atha kho te upāsakā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "They then approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.10"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te upāsakā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.11"
msgid "“ime, bhante, titthiyā avaṇṇakāmā buddhassa avaṇṇakāmā dhammassa avaṇṇakāmā saṃghassa."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, these ascetics of other sects want to disparage the Buddha, the Teaching, and the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.12"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, ayyā titthiyānaṃ sahatthā na dadeyyun”ti."
msgstr "It would be good, Venerable Sir, if the monks didn’t give anything to the ascetics of other sects from their own hands.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā te upāsake dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr "After the Master had instructed, inspired, and gladdened those lay followers with a teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.14"
msgid "Atha kho te upāsakā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr "they rose from their seats, bowed down to the him, circumambulated him with their right side towards him, and left."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.15"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.16"
msgid "“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—"
msgstr "“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.17"
msgid "saṃghasuṭṭhutāya, saṃghaphāsutāya … pe … saddhammaṭṭhitiyā, vinayānuggahāya."
msgstr "for the well-being of the Order,  for the comfort of the Order, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the restraint of corruptions in the present life, for avoiding corruptions in future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the continuation of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.18"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.18a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_868
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:1.2.19"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu acelakassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gives staple or non-staple food to a naked ascetic, to a male wanderer, or to a female wanderer with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc41.2.1, pts-vp-en.2.349, ms2V_869
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_870
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.6"
msgid "Acelako nāma"
msgstr "A naked ascetic:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.7"
msgid "yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno naggo."
msgstr "whatever wanderer is naked."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_871
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.8"
msgid "Paribbājako nāma"
msgstr "A male wanderer:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.9"
msgid "bhikkhuñca sāmaṇerañca ṭhapetvā yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno."
msgstr "any wanderer apart from Buddhist monks and novice monks."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_872
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.10"
msgid "Paribbājikā nāma"
msgstr "A female wanderer:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.11"
msgid "bhikkhuniñca sikkhamānañca sāmaṇeriñca ṭhapetvā yā kāci paribbājikasamāpannā."
msgstr "any female wanderer apart from Buddhist nuns, trainee nuns, and novice nuns."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_873
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.12"
msgid "Khādanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Non-staple food:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.13"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma."
msgstr "apart from the five staple foods, water, and tooth-cleaners, the rest is called “non-staple food.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_874
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.14"
msgid "Bhojanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Staple food:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.15"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of staple food:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.16"
msgid "odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "cooked grain, porridge, flour, fish, and meat."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_875
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.17"
msgid "Dadeyyāti"
msgstr "Gives:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.1.18"
msgid "kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he gives by body or by what is connected to the body or by releasing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc41.2.2, ms2V_876 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.1"
msgid "Titthiye titthiyasaññī sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is an ascetic from another sect, and he perceives it as an ascetic from another sect, and he gives them staple or non-staple food with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.2"
msgid "Titthiye vematiko sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is an ascetic from another sect, but he is unsure if it is, and he gives them staple or non-staple food with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.3"
msgid "Titthiye atitthiyasaññī sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is an ascetic from another sect, but he does not perceive it as an ascetic from another sect, and he gives them staple or non-staple food with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_877 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.4"
msgid "Udakadantaponaṃ deti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he gives water or tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.5"
msgid "Atitthiye titthiyasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not an ascetic from another sect, but he perceives it as an ascetic from another sect, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.6"
msgid "Atitthiye vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not an ascetic from another sect, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.2.7"
msgid "Atitthiye atitthiyasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not an ascetic from another sect, and he does not perceive it as an ascetic from another sect, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc41.2.3, pts-vp-en.2.350, ms2V_878 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.2"
msgid "dāpeti na deti,"
msgstr "if he does not give, but gets it given;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.3"
msgid "upanikkhipitvā deti,"
msgstr "if he gives by placing it near the person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.4"
msgid "bāhirālepaṃ deti,"
msgstr "if he gives ointments for external use;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.5"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.6"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_879 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:2.3.7"
msgid "Acelakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on naked ascetics, is finished."
